@{ Layout = "_LayoutUser"; }
<div class="content content-fixed content-auth-alt">
    <div class="container d-flex justify-content-center ht-100p">
        <div class=" ht-100p d-flex flex-column">

            <h4 class="tx-20 tx-sm-24">Personal Data Processing Policy</h4>
            <p class="tx-color-03 mg-b-30">
                <br><br>
                <strong>1. General Provisions</strong>
                <br><br>
                This Personal Data Processing Policy is prepared in accordance with Federal Law No. 152-FZ of
                27.07.2006 “On Personal Data” and defines the procedure for processing personal data and measures
                to ensure the security of personal data by Mikhailov Ivan Sergeevich (hereinafter – the Operator).
                <br><br>
                The Operator considers the observance of human and civil rights and freedoms during the processing
                of personal data, including the protection of the right to privacy, personal and family secrets,
                as its primary goal and condition of its activity.
                <br>
                This Policy of the Operator regarding personal data processing (hereinafter – the Policy) applies
                to all information that the Operator may receive about visitors of the website
                https://companyvd.ru.
                <br><br><br><br>

                <strong>2. Basic Terms Used in the Policy</strong>
                <br><br>
                Automated processing of personal data — processing with the use of computer technologies;
                Blocking of personal data — temporary suspension of personal data processing (except when processing
                is required for clarification of personal data);
                Website — a set of graphical and informational materials, as well as software and databases,
                accessible via https://companyvd.ru;
                Personal data information system — a set of personal data stored in databases and processed with
                information technologies and technical means;
                Anonymization of personal data — actions making it impossible to determine personal data ownership
                without additional information;
                Personal data processing — any action or set of actions performed with or without automation,
                including collection, recording, systematization, accumulation, storage, clarification (updating,
                modification), extraction, use, transfer (distribution, provision, access), anonymization,
                blocking, deletion, destruction;
                Operator — a state or municipal body, legal entity, or individual that organizes or performs
                processing of personal data, determines the purposes, scope, and actions with personal data;
                Personal data — any information relating directly or indirectly to a specific or identifiable user
                of https://companyvd.ru;
                User — any visitor of https://companyvd.ru;
                Provision of personal data — actions aimed at disclosing personal data to a specific person or
                group of persons;
                Distribution of personal data — actions aimed at disclosing personal data to an unlimited number of
                persons, including publication, posting online, or providing access in any other manner;
                Cross-border transfer of personal data — transfer of data to the territory of a foreign state,
                foreign authority, foreign natural or legal person;
                Destruction of personal data — any actions resulting in irreversible destruction of personal data
                making further recovery impossible.
                <br><br><br><br>

                <strong>3. The Operator May Process the Following Personal Data of the User</strong>
                <br><br>
                Last name, first name, patronymic;
                Phone number;
                Email address;
                The website also collects anonymized visitor data (including “cookie” files) using analytics
                services (Yandex Metrica, Google Analytics, etc.).
                <br>
                All of the above are considered Personal Data for purposes of this Policy.
                <br><br><br><br>

                <strong>4. Purposes of Personal Data Processing</strong>
                <br><br>
                The purpose of processing the User’s personal data is the conclusion, execution, and termination of
                civil-law agreements; providing access to services, information, and/or materials of
                https://companyvd.ru; clarification of order details.
                <br>
                The Operator may also send the User notifications about new products, services, special offers, and
                events. The User may unsubscribe at any time by sending an email to policy@companyvd.ru with the
                note “Unsubscribe from product and offer notifications”.
                <br>
                Anonymized data collected via analytics services is used to improve the website and its content.
                <br><br><br><br>

                <strong>5. Legal Grounds for Personal Data Processing</strong>
                <br><br>
                The Operator processes the User’s personal data only when it is submitted voluntarily through forms
                on https://companyvd.ru. By filling out these forms and/or submitting personal data, the User
                agrees to this Policy.
                <br>
                The Operator processes anonymized data when allowed by the browser settings (enabled cookies and
                JavaScript).
                <br><br><br><br>

                <strong>6. Procedure for Collection, Storage, Transfer, and Other Types of Processing</strong>
                <br><br>
                The Operator ensures personal data security through legal, organizational, and technical measures
                required for full compliance with current legislation.
                <br><br>
                The Operator ensures the confidentiality of personal data and prevents access by unauthorized
                persons.
                <br>
                Personal data will never be transferred to third parties except when required by law.
                <br>
                If inaccuracies are found in the personal data, the User may update them by sending a notification
                to policy@companyvd.ru with the note “Personal data update”.
                <br>
                Personal data processing has no time limit. The User may withdraw consent at any time by sending a
                notification to policy@companyvd.ru with the note “Withdrawal of consent for personal data
                processing”.
                <br><br><br><br>

                <strong>7. Cross-Border Transfer of Personal Data</strong>
                <br><br>
                Before transferring personal data across borders, the Operator must ensure that the foreign state
                provides reliable protection of personal data subjects’ rights.
                <br>
                Transfer to foreign states that do not meet these requirements may occur only with the User’s
                written consent and/or for the execution of a contract involving the User.
                <br><br><br><br>

                <strong>8. Final Provisions</strong>
                <br><br>
                The User may obtain any clarification on questions regarding the processing of their personal data
                by contacting the Operator via email at policy@companyvd.ru.
                <br>
                Any changes to this Policy will be reflected in this document.
                <br>
                The Policy remains valid indefinitely until replaced by a new version.
            </p>

        </div>
    </div><!-- container -->
</div><!-- content -->
